<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Research - Min-Hsiu Hsieh (謝明修)</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary-color: #2c3e50;
            --accent-color: #3498db;
            --text-color: #333;
            --bg-color: #fff;
            --light-gray: #f8f9fa;
            --border-color: #e9ecef;
        }

        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.7;
            color: var(--text-color);
            background: var(--bg-color);
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 0 20px;
        }

        /* Header */
        header {
            background: var(--primary-color);
            color: white;
            padding: 60px 0;
            text-align: center;
        }

        header h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        header .chinese-name {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            opacity: 0.9;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        header .title {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            opacity: 0.85;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        /* Navigation */
        nav {
            background: var(--light-gray);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 100;
        }

        nav ul {
            list-style: none;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 30px;
            padding: 15px 0;
        }

        nav a {
            text-decoration: none;
            color: var(--primary-color);
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: color 0.2s;
        }

        nav a:hover {
            color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        nav a.active {
            color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        /* Sections */
        section {
            padding: 40px 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }

        section:last-child {
            border-bottom: none;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            color: var(--primary-color);
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent-color);
            display: inline-block;
        }

        h3 {
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            color: var(--primary-color);
            margin: 25px 0 15px;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            text-align: justify;
        }

        /* Research Areas */
        .research-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
            gap: 25px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .research-card {
            background: var(--light-gray);
            padding: 25px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-color);
        }

        .research-card h4 {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: var(--primary-color);
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .research-card p {
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            margin-bottom: 0;
        }

        /* Back Button */
        .back-btn {
            display: inline-block;
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background: var(--accent-color);
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: background 0.2s;
        }

        .back-btn:hover {
            background: #2980b9;
        }

        /* Footer */
        footer {
            background: var(--primary-color);
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 30px 0;
            margin-top: 50px;
        }

        footer a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        /* Responsive */
        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            header h1 {
                font-size: 1.8rem;
            }

            header .chinese-name {
                font-size: 1.2rem;
            }

            nav ul {
                flex-wrap: wrap;
                gap: 15px;
            }

            h2 {
                font-size: 1.5rem;
            }

            .research-grid {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Min-Hsiu Hsieh</h1>
            <div class="chinese-name">謝明修</div>
            <div class="title">Director, Hon Hai (Foxconn) Quantum Computing Research Center</div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <div class="container">
            <ul>
                <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="about.html">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="publications.html">Publications</a></li>
                <li><a href="research.html" class="active">Research</a></li>
                <li><a href="index.html#contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <main class="container">
        <a href="index.html" class="back-btn">← Back to Home</a>

        <section id="research">
            <h2>Research Topics</h2>
            
            <p>
                My research interests include general topics in quantum information and computation. 
                At the Hon Hai (Foxconn) Quantum Computing Research Center, we are actively pursuing 
                breakthroughs in various aspects of quantum technologies.
            </p>

            <div class="research-grid">
                <div class="research-card">
                    <h4>Quantum Information Theory</h4>
                    <p>Foundational aspects of quantum information, quantum coding theory, quantum channel capacities, and quantum error correction.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="research-card">
                    <h4>Quantum Computing</h4>
                    <p>Quantum algorithms, quantum complexity theory, variational quantum circuits, and quantum machine learning.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="research-card">
                    <h4>Quantum Communication</h4>
                    <p>Quantum key distribution, quantum networks, quantum repeaters, and quantum internet protocols.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="research-card">
                    <h4>Quantum Error Correction</h4>
                    <p>Quantum LDPC codes, fault-tolerant quantum computation, and topological quantum codes.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="research-card">
                    <h4>Quantum Machine Learning</h4>
                    <p>Quantum-enhanced machine learning algorithms, tensor-train networks, and variational quantum classifiers.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="research-card">
                    <h4>Quantum Chemistry</h4>
                    <p>Quantum simulation of molecular systems, quantum algorithms for chemistry, and hybrid quantization schemes.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 40px;">Current Research Projects</h3>
            <p>
                At the Hon Hai Quantum Computing Research Center, we are currently overseeing a dozen 
                cutting-edge research projects aimed at pushing the boundaries of quantum computing. 
                Our research team comprises twenty talented researchers working on various aspects of 
                quantum technologies.
            </p>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">Collaboration</h3>
            <p>
                We maintain active collaborations with leading research institutions worldwide and 
                welcome opportunities for new partnerships. If you are interested in collaborating 
                on quantum information and computation research, please feel free to reach out.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <div class="container">
            <p>&copy; 2026 Min-Hsiu Hsieh. All rights reserved.</p>
            <p>Powered by <a href="https://pages.github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Pages</a></p>
        </div>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
